events.name: Vänskä Conducts Prokofiev + Sibelius
events.info: "Alexander Melnikov's performance [of Prokofiev] was not just compelling; it was nothing short of revelatory." (Bachtrack) The acclaimed Finnish conductor Osmo Vänskä makes a much anticipated first performance with the Atlanta Symphony Orchestra for a program of piquant rarities, beginning with the spooky and beguiling Transitions by Michigan-based conductor and composer Henry Dorn. The Orchestra welcomes Russian Music specialist Alexander Melnikov to play the Everest of piano concertos - The Piano Concerto No. 2 by Sergei Prokofiev. Then Maestro Vänskä shines the spotlight on the extraordinary musicians of the Atlanta Symphony Orchestra in the folk-inspired Symphony No. 3 by his fellow Finn Jean Sibelius.
events.pleaseNote: Osmo Vänskä Alexander Melnikov, piano Atlanta Symphony Orchestra HENRY DORN: Transitions PROKOFIEV: Piano Concerto No. 2 SIBELIUS: Symphony No. 3

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Our box office is closed for the season. Tickets can be purchased online at livenation.com.
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: General Box Office Hours: Fridays from 10 AM to 4 PM Show Day Box Office Hours: Monday to Saturday Shows: 10AM until the headliner takes the stage Sunday Shows: 12PM until the headliner takes the stage The main box office is located at 2200 Encore Parkway next to the East Gate. It can be accessed both from inside and outside of the venue. Tickets can be purchased in-person at the box office when it is open, or online at www.livenation.com.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: All main concession stands take Visa/ MasterCard / Discover and American Express. All merchandise stands take all major credit cards.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will call tickets are available for pickup at the box office located 2200 Encore Parkway (outside the East Entry Gate) generally two hours prior to the showtime.There is temporary parking located in front of the box office. Please make sure that you have a photo ID matching the purchasers name to pick up tickets. Any name changes need to go through Ticketmaster Customer Service- 800-653-8000. Guests are not permitted to put tickets in will call for other guests to pick up. You will need to arrange to meet your party at the facility to deliver tickets. If tickets or passes are being left for you- they will only be left at the box office. This includes meet and greet passes, backstage passes, press passes, and tickets from the tour or other promotional company. We do not get these tickets until the day of the event close to doors so please do not try to pick them up earlier. If your tickets/passes are not in will call you will need to contact the person that left them for you to determine where they are. The box office cannot contact any member of the tour for you.

venues.parkingDetail: Parking is preassigned. Your parking pass can be found in your Live Nation or Ticketmaster account. If you purchased your tickets elsewhere and they did not include a parking pass, you need to stop by the box office to purchase a parking pass prior to parking your vehicle. Parking spaces are first come, first serve. Patrons may notice a row or seat number on their parking pass, but that is only used for tracking purposes. There are no assigned spots on Lots A, B, C, or Premier. Physical Address- 2200 Encore Parkway Alpharetta, GA 30009. This is not the address for GPS parking directions. Instead use the following addresses to find your lot: Parking Lot A- 1755 Founders Parkway, Alpharetta, GA 30009 Parking Lot B- 1100 Sanctuary Parkway, Alpharetta, GA 30009 Parking Lot C and Premier- 11450 Maxwell Road, Alpharetta, GA 30009 VIP Parking Lot- 2300 Encore Parkway, Alpharetta, GA 30009
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating is located in Orch1, Orch3, 101, 103, and 105 row WC (There is accessible seating on the General Admission Lawn: Requires only a lawn ticket, no special ticket required).

generalInfo.generalRule: Bag Policy: To reduce staff contact with guest belongings, we have implemented the following bag policy: we will allow clear plastic, vinyl or PVC tote bags no larger than 12x6x12 and/or small clutch bags 6x9. Diaper bags are permitted for guests with babies, and they must be thoroughly searched and tagged for identification upon entry. Cashless Payments: ALL points of sale including premier parking, merchandise, food & beverage will ONLY accept debit, credit or mobile pay (Apply Pay or Google Pay). For fans that wish to use cash, cash to card conversion will be available on-site. Lawn Chair Policy: Low profile chairs are allowed (seat is 9in or less from the ground). Taller camping chairs are not allowed (seat is over 9in from the ground). If you do not have a low profile lawn chair, you can rent one in advance or at the venue (limited availability on show-days). Items ALLOWED to be brought into venue: �Clear plastic, vinyl or PVC tote bagss no larger than 12inX6inX12in or small clutch bags (6inX9in). �small, personal size umbrellas �Water: Up to 1 (one) liter in a factory sealed bottle. Empty refillable aluminum and plastic water bottles are also permitted �Cameras: nonprofessional only, no detachable lenses �Lawn Chairs: low profile (seat no more than 9 inches off the ground) �Small blankets no larger than 4ftx8ft Items NOT ALLOWED to be brought into venue include, but are not limited to: �Weapons of any kind (including wallet chains, mace, pepper spray) �No frisbees nor footballs �Large or golf size umbrellas, nor umbrellas with a point on the end. �iPads, Go-Pros, drones, recording devices �Alcohol �Illegal drugs/substances �Glass containers �Cans �Coolers �Bags that do not meet the bag policy description �Laser pointers �Animals (except service animals) �Fireworks �Chains �Spikes �Food (food for dietary health issues may be allowed in a 1 (one) gallon clear plastic bag)

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: General Box Office Hours: Fridays from 10 AM to 4 PM Show Day Box Office Hours: Monday to Saturday Shows: 10AM until the headliner takes the stage Sunday Shows: 12PM until the headliner takes the stage The main box office is located at 2200 Encore Parkway next to the East Gate. It can be accessed both from inside and outside of the venue. Tickets can be purchased in-person at the box office when it is open, or online at www.livenation.com.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: All main concession stands take Visa/ MasterCard / Discover and American Express. All merchandise stands take all major credit cards.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will call tickets are available for pickup at the box office located 2200 Encore Parkway (outside the East Entry Gate) generally two hours prior to the showtime.There is temporary parking located in front of the box office. Please make sure that you have a photo ID matching the purchasers name to pick up tickets. Any name changes need to go through Ticketmaster Customer Service- 800-653-8000. Guests are not permitted to put tickets in will call for other guests to pick up. You will need to arrange to meet your party at the facility to deliver tickets. If tickets or passes are being left for you- they will only be left at the box office. This includes meet and greet passes, backstage passes, press passes, and tickets from the tour or other promotional company. We do not get these tickets until the day of the event close to doors so please do not try to pick them up earlier. If your tickets/passes are not in will call you will need to contact the person that left them for you to determine where they are. The box office cannot contact any member of the tour for you.

venues.parkingDetail: Parking is preassigned. Your parking pass can be found in your Live Nation or Ticketmaster account. If you purchased your tickets elsewhere and they did not include a parking pass, you need to stop by the box office to purchase a parking pass prior to parking your vehicle. Parking spaces are first come, first serve. Patrons may notice a row or seat number on their parking pass, but that is only used for tracking purposes. There are no assigned spots on Lots A, B, C, or Premier. Physical Address- 2200 Encore Parkway Alpharetta, GA 30009. This is not the address for GPS parking directions. Instead use the following addresses to find your lot: Parking Lot A- 1755 Founders Parkway, Alpharetta, GA 30009 Parking Lot B- 1100 Sanctuary Parkway, Alpharetta, GA 30009 Parking Lot C and Premier- 11450 Maxwell Road, Alpharetta, GA 30009 VIP Parking Lot- 2300 Encore Parkway, Alpharetta, GA 30009
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating is located in Orch1, Orch3, 101, 103, and 105 row WC (There is accessible seating on the General Admission Lawn: Requires only a lawn ticket, no special ticket required).

generalInfo.generalRule: Bag Policy: To reduce staff contact with guest belongings, we have implemented the following bag policy: we will allow clear plastic, vinyl or PVC tote bags no larger than 12x6x12 and/or small clutch bags 6x9. Diaper bags are permitted for guests with babies, and they must be thoroughly searched and tagged for identification upon entry. Cashless Payments: ALL points of sale including premier parking, merchandise, food & beverage will ONLY accept debit, credit or mobile pay (Apply Pay or Google Pay). For fans that wish to use cash, cash to card conversion will be available on-site. Lawn Chair Policy: Low profile chairs are allowed (seat is 9in or less from the ground). Taller camping chairs are not allowed (seat is over 9in from the ground). If you do not have a low profile lawn chair, you can rent one in advance or at the venue (limited availability on show-days). Items ALLOWED to be brought into venue: �Clear plastic, vinyl or PVC tote bagss no larger than 12inX6inX12in or small clutch bags (6inX9in). �small, personal size umbrellas �Water: Up to 1 (one) liter in a factory sealed bottle. Empty refillable aluminum and plastic water bottles are also permitted �Cameras: nonprofessional only, no detachable lenses �Lawn Chairs: low profile (seat no more than 9 inches off the ground) �Small blankets no larger than 4ftx8ft Items NOT ALLOWED to be brought into venue include, but are not limited to: �Weapons of any kind (including wallet chains, mace, pepper spray) �No frisbees nor footballs �Large or golf size umbrellas, nor umbrellas with a point on the end. �iPads, Go-Pros, drones, recording devices �Alcohol �Illegal drugs/substances �Glass containers �Cans �Coolers �Bags that do not meet the bag policy description �Laser pointers �Animals (except service animals) �Fireworks �Chains �Spikes �Food (food for dietary health issues may be allowed in a 1 (one) gallon clear plastic bag)
generalInfo.childRule: All of our events are all ages. Children 2 and under do not require a ticket but must sit on a parent's lap.

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: 404-878-3000 - State Farm Arena Box Office 1-866-715-1500 - Atlanta Hawks
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Box Office is open on event days and for the first day of all on-sales. (Hours will vary based upon the events and time of on-sales).
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Accepts: cash, Visa, Mastercard, Discover, American Express
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Located at main box office on Centennial Olympic Park Drive. Available for pickup beginning 1 1/2 hours prior to event. Closing time will vary by event. PLEASE BRING A PICTURE ID, THE ACTUAL CREDIT CARD USED TO PURCHASE THE TICKETS, AND YOUR ORDER NUMBER.

venues.parkingDetail: Parking is available in various lots around State Farm Arena including Centennial Garage and the CNN Deck located on Centennial Olympic Park Drive across from the arena. Both lots may be entered from Centennial Olympic Park Drive or Spring Street. Accessible parking is available in both lots. Price varies by event. The Philips Lot, located beneath the CNN Parking lot area, directly across from State Farm Arena, is adjacent to “The Gulch” and can be entered from the downward ramp on Centennial Olympic Park Drive.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating is available in throughout the arena in various price categories. Seating for the sight/hearing impaired available in the lower level. All accessible seating is subject to availability. All levels of the Arena are accessible by elevator and escalator.

generalInfo.generalRule: No smoking inside arena. No glass bottles, aluminum cans, coolers, thermoses, outside food, or alcoholic beverages No banners or laser pointers. No Backpacks.
generalInfo.childRule: For most events, everyone two and older must have a ticket. For Sesame Street Live, children one and older must have a ticket. Please see the ticket information for each event.

PLEASE BRING A PICTURE ID, THE ACTUAL CREDIT CARD USED TO PURCHASE THE TICKETS, AND YOUR ORDER NUMBER.

venues.parkingDetail: Limited parking is available in lots surrounding the amphitheater and curbside. All parking is $25. Please DO NOT Block driveways! Please observe the no parking signs!
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible area is in right orchestra, Row T No special arrangements available for mobility impaired or hearing/sight impaired patrons.

generalInfo.generalRule: Chastain 2023 Allowable Policies: Non-Carry In Events (No tables, row on row, "rock and roll setup") Allowed: Average sized bags/ backpacks (subject to search), Average sized blankets or beach towels, Cameras- non-professional only, no detachable lenses, Umbrellas- personal sized only, no sharp points. Water- 1 factory sealed bottle up to 1 liter in size. Not Allowed: Weapons, Alcoho,l Illegal Drugs, Glass containers or cans, Coolers, Large Bags or Backpacks, Laser Pointers, Animals (Except service animals), Fireworks, Strollers, Signs larger than 8.5" x 11". Carry In Events (Tables Shows) Allowed: 1 Cooler per person, no larger than 23" long and 16" deep, subject to search at the gates, TV Trays are allowed only in orchestra seating (no box seats, pit seats or lawn seats) and tray must be smaller than 23" x 16", Food, Candles with a covered flame (no open flame), Plastic cutlery and cups (no metal or glass), Beverages, including alcohol (beer, wine and liquor bottles smaller than 375ml or 1 pint), Average sized bags/ backpacks (subject to search), Average sized blankets or beach towels, Cameras- non-professional only, no detachable lenses, Umbrellas- personal sized only, no sharp point. Not Allowed: Open Flames, Glasswear Liquor Bottles larger than 375ml or 1 pint, Weapons, Illegal Drugs, Large Bags or Backpacks, Laser Pointers, Animals (Except service animals), Fireworks, Strollers, Signs larger than 8.5" x 11". All allowed items are subject to change at the venue's discretion without prior notification. Please call the venue ahead of your show with any questions.
generalInfo.childRule: Children of ALL ages need a ticket - even a baby in arms.
